# Cursor AI Rules for Hunter Service

## Project Context
API test automation framework using Java 11, Playwright, TestNG, and Cucumber for testing GoREST API.

## Critical Rules

### 1. Playwright API Usage
- NEVER concatenate RequestOptions objects to URL strings
- Always pass RequestOptions as second parameter: `apiContext.get(url, options)`
- Example: ❌ `url + "?" + requestOptions` | ✅ `apiContext.get(url, requestOptions)`

### 2. Code Structure
- API helpers in `Helaper/` package (note spelling)
- Validations in `Validation/` package
- Constants in `constants/` package
- Follow existing package naming (some start with capital)

### 3. Response Validation
- Use Jackson ObjectMapper for JSON parsing
- Validate ALL fields when comparing responses (id, name, email, gender, status)
- Provide descriptive assertion messages with context
- When validating by ID match, compare all other fields too

### 4. Logging & Reporting
- Every API call needs console logging + Allure reporting
- Log: URL, curl command, status, response body
- Use Allure.step() and Allure.addAttachment()

### 5. Best Practices
- Read entire file before editing
- Maintain existing naming conventions exactly
- Use TestNG assertions with clear messages
- Handle JSON arrays with proper iteration
- Store test data in CSV files under `data/`

## Quick Reference
- Java 11 syntax
- Maven commands: `mvn test`, `mvn allure:serve`
- Base URL: https://gorest.co.in/public/v2
- Testing framework: TestNG + Cucumber